%20day%20on%20record.%20Just%2024%20hours%20later%2C%20that%20record%20broke%20again%20making%20last%20Monday%20very%20likely%20the%20hottest%20day%20in%20thousands%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20improbable%20for%20scientists%20to%20gauge%20the%20world's%20hottest%20day%20given%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20temperature%20monitors%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20world%20and%20less%20than%20a%20century%20of%20relatively%20widespread%20observations.%20But%20they've%20developed%20a%20technique%20that's%20increasingly%20useful%20as%20the%20planet%20heats%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20month's%20shocking%20heat%20findings%2C%20announced%20by%20the%20EU's%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%2C%20are%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Breanalysis%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20technique%20that%20mixes%20temperature%20data%20and%20models%20to%20provide%20a%20global%20view%20of%20the%20climate.%20The%20center%20creates%20a%20nearly%20real-time%20picture%20of%20the%20Earth's%20climate%2C%20including%20temperature%2C%20wind%20and%20precipitation%2C%20for%20(roughly)%20every%2030-square-kilometer%20chunk%20of%20the%20planet's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20reanalysis%20goes%20back%20to%201940%2C%20and%20it%20allows%20researchers%20to%20say%20with%20confidence%20when%20a%20record%20is%20broken%2C%20whether%20for%20a%20day%2C%20month%20or%20year.%20Beyond%20the%20new%20daily%20heat%20record%2C%20the%20data%20also%20shows%20that%202023%20was%20the%20hottest%20year%20ever%20recorded%20and%20that%20every%20calendar%20month%20for%20the%20past%2013%20months%20has%20been%20the%20hottest%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20there%20aren't%20thermometers%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20world%2C%20Copernicus%20receives%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20weather%20data%20that%20it%20uses%20to%20underpin%20its%20reanalysis.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20this%20constant%20flow%20of%20information%20coming%20into%20the%20center%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Carlo%20Buontempo%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Climate%20Change%20Service%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20European%20Centre%20for%20Medium-Range%20Weather%20Forecasts%20(ECMWF).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20at%20the%20center%20receive%20100%20million%20readings%20per%20day%20about%20weather%20conditions%20from%20around%20the%20world.%20Observations%20come%20from%20airplanes%2C%20satellites%2C%20ships%2C%20radar%20and%20surface-level%20weather%20stations%20-%20all%20feeding%20real-time%20information%20about%20temperature%2C%20wind%2C%20rain%20and%20snow%20information%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20factors%20like%20air%20pollution.%20This%20information%20is%20fed%20into%20a%20model%2C%20known%20as%20ERA5%2C%20which%20is%20already%20equipped%20with%20historic%20information%20about%20the%20global%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20gaps%20in%20these%20observations%20because%20the%20data%20sources%20don't%20cover%20every%20part%20of%20the%20world.%20Weather%20conditions%20like%20cloudy%20skies%20may%20also%20reduce%20the%20amount%20of%20data%20coming%20from%20sources%20like%20satellites.%20To%20fill%20these%20gaps%2C%20the%20scientists%20take%20the%20predictions%20they%20have%20already%20made%2C%20based%20on%20the%20long-term%20ERA5%20model%2C%20and%20test%20them%20against%20the%20observations.%20That%20means%20a%20forecast%20that%20predicts%20a%20particular%20temperature%20in%20a%20particular%20place%20will%20be%20tested%20against%20all%20the%20data%20researchers%20receive%20about%20the%20weather%20in%20that%20place%20and%20nearby%2C%20as%20well%20as%20broader%20forces%20like%20ocean%20currents%20and%20air%20circulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20done%20repeatedly%20while%20assessing%20how%20compatible%20the%20prediction%20is%20with%20what's%20actually%20been%20recorded.%20The%20model%20also%20accounts%20for%20any%20errors%20in%20the%20recorded%20data%2C%20and%20relies%20on%20the%20laws%20of%20physics%2C%20including%20the%20weather%20patterns%2C%20currents%20and%20airflow%20that%20govern%20how%20the%20global%20climate%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20it's%20possible%20to%20create%20a%20complete%20picture%20that%20is%20as%20accurate%20as%20possible.%20That's%20what%20allows%20scientists%20to%20confidently%20declare%20records%20like%20when%20the%20world%20experiences%20the%20hottest%20day%20in%20human%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20five%20weather%20services%20-%20the%20US's%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20and%20NASA%2C%20the%20ECMWF%2C%20the%20China%20Meteorological%20Administration%2C%20and%20the%20Japan%20Meteorological%20Agency%20-%20carry%20out%20continuous%20appraisals%20of%20global%20temperature%20using%20this%20technique.%20While%20their%20models%20differ%20slightly%2C%20the%20five%20groups%20have%20come%20to%20similar%20conclusions%20about%20record%20heat%20in%20recent%20months%20and%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorical%20data%20is%20trickier%20to%20come%20by.%20The%20longest-running%20temperature%20series%2C%20the%20Central%20England%20Temperature%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20started%20in%20the%2017th%20century.%20Data%20from%20before%20humans%20were%20systematically%20monitoring%20temperatures%20comes%20from%20sources%20like%20bubbles%20of%20gas%20trapped%20in%20glacial%20ice%2C%20or%20tree%20rings.%20These%20sources%20aren't%20as%20specific%20as%20a%20thermometer%20reading%2C%20but%20it's%20possible%20to%20say%20with%20confidence%20that%20recent%20temperatures%20are%20likely%20the%20highest%20in%20around%20100%2C000%20years%2C%20Copernicus%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeteorologists%20also%20have%20a%20good%20idea%20when%20a%20particularly%20significant%20day%2C%20like%20the%20hottest%20day%20on%20record%2C%20is%20on%20its%20way.%20This%20is%20partly%20because%20global%20mean%20temperatures%20usually%20peak%20between%20early%20July%20and%20early%20August.%20Last%20year's%20hottest%20day%20-%20which%20was%20the%20previous%20record%20for%20the%20hottest%20ever%20-%20occurred%20in%20early%20July%20amid%20a%20historic%20oceanic%20heat%20wave.%20An%20intensifying%20El%20Nino%20-%20a%20natural%20global%20climate%20phenomenon%20that%20usually%20means%20hotter%20temperatures%20globally%20-%20provided%20yet%20another%20clue%20that%20record%20heat%20was%20brewing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20this%20July%2C%20it%20looked%20for%20a%20while%20like%20the%20world%20wouldn't%20set%20a%20new%20daily%20record%2C%20says%20Buontempo.%20%26quot%3BThe%20global%20mean%20temperature%20for%20the%20oceans%20started%20rising%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20people%20who%20systematically%20monitor%20our%20predictions%20started%20to%20sound%20alarm%20bells.%26quot%3B%20By%20the%20start%20of%20last%20week%2C%20they%20were%20paying%20extra%20attention%20to%20the%20reanalysis%20and%20getting%20ready%20to%20make%20an%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20technique%20isn't%20just%20useful%20for%20making%20%26quot%3Bhottest%20day%20ever%26quot%3B%20announcements%3A%20It's%20being%20used%20to%20train%20AI%20forecasting%20models%2C%20especially%20for%20%26quot%3Bensemble%26quot%3B%20weather%20forecasts%2C%20which%20represent%20multiple%20possible%20future%20scenarios.%20It's%20also%20used%20by%20solar%20energy%20companies%20to%20help%20homeowners%20work%20out%20how%20much%20energy%20their%20panels%20might%20generate%2C%20and%20by%20wind%20energy%20companies%20to%20plan%20where%20to%20put%20wind%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECopernicus%20is%20currently%20working%20on%20a%20new%20model%2C%20known%20as%20ERA6%2C%20which%20will%20be%20more%20precise%20-%20dividing%20the%20world%20into%2014%20kilometer%20squares%20-%20and%20incorporate%20many%20more%20historic%20data%20sources%2C%20including%20early%20satellite%20readings%20from%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Buontempo%2C%20more%20important%20than%20any%20one%20day%20is%20the%20recent%20extraordinary%20streak%20of%20record-breaking%20months%2C%20given%20that's%20a%20better%20indicator%20o