0BI%20it'd%20graded%20at%20least%206%20million%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20in%202023%20alone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20boom%20came%20as%20more%C2%A0'90s%20kids%20began%20making%20money%20to%20spend%20on%20their%20childhood%20hobbies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID%20pandemic%20was%20an%20unprecedented%20boom%20for%20the%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20card%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStuck%20at%20home%2C%20collectors%20went%20into%20a%20trading%20overdrive%20and%20pushed%20prices%20up%20nearly%20500%25.%20Few%20can%20forget%20the%20%243.5%20million%20YouTuber-boxer%20Logan%20Paul%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flogan-paul-35-million-box-pokemon-cards-he-bought-fake-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblew%20on%20a%20pack%20of%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20GI%20Joe%20collectibles.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20degree%20of%20card%20fever%20has%20waned%20post-pandemic.%20But%20the%20momentum%20in%20renewed%20interest%20for%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20has%20turned%20them%20into%20the%20world's%20largest%20collectibles%20market%2C%20at%20least%20according%20to%20grading%20company%20Professional%20Sports%20Authenticators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20basically%20gone%20from%20zero%20to%20a%20third%20of%20our%20volume%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20Hoge%2C%20president%20of%20PSA%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsidered%20the%20leading%20authority%20on%20the%20physical%20condition%20of%20millions%20of%20collectibles%2C%20PSA's%20word%20is%20the%20law%20when%20collectors%20assess%20the%20quality%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therefore%20price%20%E2%80%94%20of%20a%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20says%20it%20receives%2075%25%20of%20all%20cards%20sent%20for%20grading%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20its%20teams%20of%20experts%20look%20into%20every%20aspect%20of%20a%20card's%20appearance%2C%20from%20folds%20and%20creases%20to%20the%20luster%20of%20its%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20much%20of%20PSA's%2035-year%20history%2C%20sports%20memorabilia%20like%20baseball%20and%20basketball%20cards%20were%20top%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Hoge%20says%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20is%20now%20the%20largest%20category%20of%20cards%20being%20graded%2C%20fueling%20a%20surge%20in%20overall%20demand%20since%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202015%2C%20PSA%20put%20out%20a%20release%20saying%20we%20just%20graded%20our%2025%20millionth%20collectible.%20It%20took%20us%2024%20years%20to%20do%20that.%20In%202023%20alone%2C%20we%20graded%2014%20million%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20estimated%20that%20last%20year%2C%20PSA%20graded%20at%20least%206%20million%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20trading%20cards%20out%20of%20the%20total%2014%20million%20it%20processed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-src%3D%5C%22visualisation%2F18668844%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ELaunched%20as%20a%20video%20game%20series%20in%201996%20for%20Nintendo's%20Gameboy%20handheld%2C%20the%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20brand%20has%20evolved%20into%20a%20mega-franchise%20of%20films%2C%20amusement%20parks%2C%20and%20trading%20cards%20that%20made%20an%20estimated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.licenseglobal.com%2Frankings-lists%2Ftop-150-leading-licensors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2411.6%20billion%20last%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20made%20a%20lifetime%20total%20of%20more%20than%2064.8%20billion%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20since%201999%2C%20and%20production%20has%20been%20accelerating%20rapidly%20since%20the%20pandemic.%20Over%2030%20billion%20of%20its%20cards%20were%20created%20after%202019%2C%20including%2011.9%20billion%20in%20its%202023%20fiscal%20year%20ending%20in%20March%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.pokemon.co.jp%2Fen%2Faboutus%2Ffigures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20updates%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20competitor%20makes%20notes%20while%20playing%20Pokemon%20on%20a%20Nintendo%20Switch%20console%20during%20the%202022%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20World%20Championships%20at%20ExCel%20on%20August%2018%2C%202022%20in%20London%2C%20England.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668272481f0c1cd6d7301a18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20competitor%20makes%20notes%20while%20playing%20Pokemon%20on%20a%20Nintendo%20Switch%20console%20during%20the%202022%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20World%20Championships%20in%20London.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Keeble%2FGetty%20Images)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHoge%20said%20that%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20most%20PSA%20customers%20sending%20in%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20collectibles%20would%20reserve%20grading%20only%20for%20the%20rarest%2C%20most%20valuable%2C%20and%20pristine%20trophy%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20now%20you're%20seeing%20more%20people%20grading%2C%20say%2C%20the%20full%20art%20cards%20that%20you%20can%20get%20out%20of%20newer%20packs%2C%20the%20newer%20boxes%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20the%20submissions%20received%20by%20PSA%20this%20year%20are%20from%20new%20customers%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224aa376a1-e006-48c6-979e-961059df4729%5C%22%3EBig%20business%20for%20nostalgia-craving%20millennials%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20typically%20spend%20about%205%25%20of%20their%20card's%20value%20on%20grading%2C%20and%20it%20costs%20a%20minimum%20of%20%2415%20to%20send%20in%20a%20collectible%20to%20PSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Hoge%2C%20PSA%20caps%20its%20prices%20at%20a%20%24500%2C000%20card%20value%2C%20so%20record-breaking%20cards%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flogan-paul-fight-5-million-pokemon-card-world-record-wrestlemania-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPikachu%20that%20sold%20for%20%245.2%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20fetch%20the%20company%20%24250%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20customers%20wait%20a%20maximum%20of%20two%20months%20for%20their%20graded%20card%2C%20which%20returns%20with%20a%20rating%20between%201%20and%2010.%20A%20higher%20number%20indicates%20better%20quality%2C%20with%2010%20representing%20brand-new%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20rating%20usually%20determines%20the%20sale%20price%20of%20a%20collectible.%20One%20mint-condition%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20card%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharizard-1999-pokemon-card-auctions-420000-mint-condition-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erating%20of%2010%20sold%20for%20%24420%2C000%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20though%20more%20than%20100%20copies%20of%20the%20same%20card%20on%20the%20market%20bore%20the%20same%20grading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20most%20valuable%20card%20in%20Jens%20Ishoey%20Prehn's%20collection%20of%2035%2C000%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20is%20pictured%20in%20Niva%2C%20eastern%20Denmark%20on%20November%2025%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668271781aace5b3ada2fbc1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20most%20valuable%20card%20in%20Jens%20Ishoey%20Prehn's%20collection%20of%2035%2C000%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20is%20pictured%20in%20Niva%2C%20eastern%20Denmark%2C%20on%20November%2025%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EIDA%20MARIE%20ODGAARD%2FRitzau%20Scanpix%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20prices%20like%20these%2C%20some%20buyers%20see%20the%20card%20trophies%20as%20potential%20for%20investment%2C%20in%20the%20same%20vein%20as%20art%20collecting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Hoge%20said%20much%20of%20the%20recent%20burst%20in%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20card%20collecting%20stems%20from%20younger%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20diving%20back%20into%20their%20old%20hobbies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecades%20after%20Pok%C3%A9mon's%20first%20trading%20cards%20were%20released%20in%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20young%20enthusiasts%20from%20that%20day%20and%20age%20are%20now%20adults%20and%20have%20money%20to%20spend%2C%20Hoge%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNostalgia%20plays%20a%20really%20key%20factor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20reach%20a%20certain%20age%20%E2%80%94%20typically%20it's%20when%20they%20get%20to%20their%20early%2030s%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20have%20some%20disposable%20income%2C%20they%20reminisce%20on%20their%20childhoods%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20go%20back%20to%20something%20they%20enjoyed%20as%20a%20kid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b235cf89-7838-41a3-9ac6-35f730d12e2f%5C%22%3EOutlasting%20the%20'90s%20kid%20generation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20growth%20has%20been%20so%20stark%20that%20PSA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fpsacardtcg%2Fp%2FC4LvLF7PAOB%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20a%20magazine%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E%20covering%20only%20trading%20card%20games.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20its%20main%20monthly%20magazine%2C%20dedicated%20to%20sports%20memorabilia%2C%20may%20at%20most%20have%20featured%20one%20or%20two%20articles%20on%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20per%20issue%2C%20Hoge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrading%20card%20submissions%20from%20Japan%20%E2%80%94%20for%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20and%20other%20games%20related%20to%20animes%20like%20%26quot%3BOne%20Piece%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BYu-Gi-Oh!%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20have%20also%20jumped.%20PSA%2C%20which%20traditionally%20stationed%20its%20graders%20and%20experts%20in%20California%2C%20has%20been%20expanding%20its%20Tokyo%20office%20of%20eight%20people%20to%20about%20110%20staff%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Competito