%20receive%20FDA%20approval%2C%20which%20could%20prompt%20easier%20access%20for%20more%20patients%2C%20since%20Medicare%20and%20insurance%20companies%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20cover%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20can%20be%20completed%20via%20a%20blood%20draw%20at%20a%20routine%20medical%20exam%2C%20making%20it%20less%20invasive%20than%20a%20colonoscopy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20works%20by%20detecting%20signals%20of%20cancer%20in%20the%20blood%2C%20such%20as%20DNA%20shed%20by%20tumors%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Guardant%20fact%20sheet.%20However%2C%20it's%20more%20effective%20at%20flagging%20later-stage%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20other%20testing%2C%20as%20patients%20will%20still%20need%20a%20colonoscopy%20to%20confirm%20a%20diagnosis%2C%20it%20could%20help%20close%20the%20gap%20between%20patients%20who%20could%20benefit%20from%20screening%20and%20those%20who%20actually%20complete%20the%20recommended%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20David%20Chung%2C%20a%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%20professor%20who%20published%20research%20on%20the%20test%20supported%20by%20Guardant%2C%20called%20the%20FDA%20approval%20a%20%26quot%3Btremendous%20leap%20forward%26quot%3B%20in%20screening%20options%20for%20colorectal%20cancer%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20life-saving%20early%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20decision%20will%20help%20make%20screening%20tests%20more%20broadly%20accessible%20and%20propel%20blood-based%20testing%20and%20CRC%20screening%20into%20a%20new%20era%2C%26quot%3B%20Chung%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BWith%20increased%20screening%20rates%20and%20early%20cancer%20detection%2C%20many%20more%20lives%20can%20be%20saved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2253dfb30d-921c-428f-919b-c028238290a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EColon%20cancer%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20and%20early%20treatment%20is%20key%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EColorectal%20cancer%20is%20expected%20to%20cause%20more%20than%20