%20straw%2C%20soil%20and%20water%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-2_11zon-1721812497.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-2_11zon-1721812497-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-2_11zon-1721812497-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-2_11zon-1721812497-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-2_11zon-1721812497-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358214%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20built%20with%20cob%2C%20which%20is%20a%20mixture%20of%20sand%2C%20clay%2C%20straw%2C%20soil%20and%20water%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKnock%20on%20sustainability%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20passed%20by%20Dhunar%20Gaon%20in%20Rishikesh%20in%202021%2C%20was%20met%20with%20an%20unusual%20sight.%20Albanian%20folk%20songs%20reverberated%20through%20the%20air%2C%20interrupted%20only%20by%20the%20beats%20of%20Japanese%20rock%20music%2C%20German%20techno%2C%20and%20Daler%20Mehndi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ETunak%20Tunak%20Tun%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20grooving%20to%20these%20lively%20tempos%20were%20a%20group%20of%2090%20individuals.%20A%20closer%20look%20at%20them%20would%20reveal%20their%20vivid%20origins%20%E2%80%94%20Brazil%2C%20Australia%2C%20Germany%2C%20France%2C%20Canada%2C%20Slovenia%20%E2%80%94%2018%20nationalities%2C%20to%20be%20precise%2C%20Ansh%20states.%20Their%20rhythms%20though%20unchoreographed%2C%20would%20seem%20almost%20synced%20to%20an%20onlooker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20don%E2%80%99t%20be%20distracted%20by%20their%20moves%2C%20Ansh%20urges%2C%20look%20under%20their%20feet%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FOtYaplok1Z8%3Fsi%3DtIHOIpE9o8aOTj38%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20the%20material%20the%20group%20spent%20months%20dancing%20upon%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CCob%20is%20a%20mixture%20of%20clay%2C%20sand%2C%20soil%2C%20straw%20and%20water.%20We%20chopped%20wheat%20and%20rice%20straw%2C%20put%20it%20on%20a%20tarp%2C%20and%20then%20invited%20the%20group%20to%20dance%20on%20it%20until%20it%20formed%20a%20burrito-shaped%20dough.%20Once%20stable%2C%20the%20dough%20does%20not%20break%20and%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20building%20material.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20they%20brought%20in%20foreign%20hands%20for%20the%20project%2C%20Raghav%20laughs%20and%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20planned.%20We%20put%20out%20a%20request%20on%20the%20website%20%E2%80%98Workaway%E2%80%99%2C%20asking%20people%20interested%20in%20sustainable%20building%20to%20join%20us.%20Through%20the%20months%2C%20we%20got%20many%20who%20were%20keen%20on%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20these%20were%20people%20who%20did%20not%20specially%20make%20a%20trip%20to%20dance%20on%20the%20cob.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20already%20heading%20to%20Rishikesh%20for%20a%20vacation.%20But%20their%20interest%20in%20natural%20building%20attracted%20them%20to%20our%20site.%20We%20set%20up%20a%20dorm%20for%20them%20in%20the%20village%20Umrisen%2C%20where%20we%20were%20camping%20out%20during%20the%20construction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAishwarya%20Lakhani%2C%20an%20interior%20designer%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20was%20a%20part%20of%20this%20community%20effort%2C%20says%20she%20had%20always%20been%20meaning%20to%20get%20into%20conscious%20design.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20came%20across%20this%20project%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20opportunity.%20I%20had%20been%20wanting%20to%20go%20to%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20for%20months%20and%20since%20it%20was%20coinciding%20with%20my%20Rishikesh%20travel%20dates%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20head%20there.%20Right%20from%20day%20one%2C%20it%20was%20a%20warm%20experience%20staying%20with%20the%20villagers.%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20took%20good%20care%20of%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20echoes%20the%20thoughts%20of%20the%20others%20when%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20in%20awe%20that%20such%20a%20thing%20could%20be%20achieved%20in%20a%20remote%20location.%20Having%20practised%20with%20reusable%20materials%20and%20natural%20plasters%20myself%2C%20it%20%5Bthis%20project%5D%20gave%20me%20hope%20and%20inspiration%20knowing%20that%20the%20sky%20is%20the%20limit%20when%20using%20cob%20for%20built%20environments.%20Working%20with%20cob%20grounds%20you.%20Dancing%20on%20the%20mud%20is%20an%20emotion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBharat%20Rolaniya%2C%20an%20architect%2C%20seconds%20Lakhani.%20%E2%80%9CWorking%20with%20mud%2C%20specifically%20cob%20was%20very%20intuitive%20to%20me.%20Being%20a%20natural%20building%20construction%20practitioner%2C%20I%20enjoyed%20working%20with%20cob.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20like%20finding%20yourself.%20In%20architecture%2C%20one%20tends%20to%20feel%20like%20they%20are%20transforming%20a%20building%2C%20but%20working%20with%20mud%20and%20cob%20shows%20you%20that%20it%20goes%20both%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20they%20transform%20you%20in%20turn%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20the%20brother%20duo%20three%20years%20to%20build%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort.%20They%20recall%20the%20journey%20as%20revelationary%20in%20many%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20two%20city%20kids%20who%20did%20not%20know%20much%2C%20we%20learnt%20a%20lot%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ansh.%20%E2%80%9CTravelling%20from%20the%20last%20motorable%20point%20in%20Phoolchatti%20to%20the%20Umrisen%20village%20involved%20crossing%20a%20wooden%20bridge%20across%20a%20tributary%20Heval%20and%20then%20hiking%20for%201.5%20km.%20Each%20time%20we%20had%20to%20get%20groceries%2C%20we%20had%20to%20make%20a%2020%20km%20trek.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20effort%20was%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20comprises%20a%20loft%20bed%2C%20a%20cave%20bedroom%2C%20a%20kitchenette%2C%20and%20a%20bathroom%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-3-1721812808-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358224%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETiny%20Farm%20Fort%20comprises%20a%20loft%20bed%2C%20a%20cave%20bedroom%2C%20a%20kitchenette%2C%20and%20a%20bathroom%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20concept%20of%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20to%20showcase%20the%20properties%20of%20sustainable%20and%20natural%20building%20materials%20such%20as%20cob%20in%20modern-day%20structures%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-4-1721812886-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358226%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20concept%20of%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20to%20showcase%20the%20properties%20of%20sustainable%20and%20natural%20building%20materials%20such%20as%20cob%20in%20modern-day%20structures%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20a%20masterpiece.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20a%20work%20of%20many%20hands%2C%E2%80%9D%20points%20out%20Raghav.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20spend%20almost%20six%20to%20eight%20hours%20building%20the%20home%20and%20never%20took%20a%20day%20off.%20Whether%20it%20was%20hot%20sun%20with%20temperatures%20crossing%2044%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20raining%2C%20or%20even%20dark%20and%20cold%20in%20winter%20%E2%80%94%20nothing%20stopped%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20add%20to%20it%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20easy%20being%20outsiders%20in%20a%20village.%20But%20instead%20of%20resisting%20guidance%2C%20Raghav%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20let%20the%20villagers%20take%20over.%E2%80%9D%20And%20as%20the%20brothers%20soon%20realised%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20wisdom%20to%20be%20gleaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20let%20them%20teach%20us%20farming%2C%20how%20to%20use%20tools%20for%20construction%2C%20how%20to%20pick%20up%20rocks%2C%20break%20them%2C%20and%20then%20build%20a%20frugal%20trolley%20to%20transport%20these%20rocks%2C%20bamboo%20and%20wooden%20logs%20back%20and%20forth.%20We%20learnt%20how%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Erotis%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20flatbread)%20using%20a%20%3Cem%3Echula%20%3C%2Fem%3E(earthen%20stove)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%202024%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20was%20ready%20to%20host%20its%20first%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20planning%20to%20make%20a%20trip%20here%2C%20full%20disclosure%3A%20reaching%20the%20homestay%20from%20Heval%20involves%20a%2030-minute%20trek%2C%20with%20some%20pockets%20posing%20a%20steep%20climb.%20But%20the%20beauty%20compensates%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20set%20foot%20into%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%2C%20%3Cem%3Edeja%20vu%3C%2Fem%3E%20will%20creep%20up%20on%20you%2C%20making%20all%20those%20fairy%20tales%20seem%20believable%20at%20long%20last.%20In%20every%20sense%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20impersonates%20a%20goblin%E2%80%99s%20den%2C%20and%20you%20might%20almost%20expect%20to%20see%20one%20hanging%20around%20during%20your%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20homestay%20is%20cradled%20by%20a%20mountain%20forest%20and%20perched%20high%20on%20a%20ridge%20such%20that%20it%20overlooks%20an%20expanse%20of%20emerald%20%E2%80%94%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20river%20Ganges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20coolness%20engulfs%20the%20home%20in%20the%20summers%2C%20while%20an%20ambient%20temperature%20is%20maintained%20during%20the%20winters%20%E2%80%94%20gratis%20the%2019-inch%20thick%20mud%20walls.%20As%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20iterate%2C%20the%20home%20was%20designed%20with%20an%20open%20plan%20in%20mind%20with%20a%20cosy%20loft%20bed%20and%20a%20cave-like%20bedroom%20(which%20accommodates%20two%20people%20each)%2C%20a%20kitchenette%20with%20pots%20and%20pans%2C%20an%20outdoor%20barbeque%2C%20a%20woodfire%20pizza%20oven%20%E2%80%94%20made%20completely%20from%20mud%20%E2%80%94%20a%20rooftop%20garden%2C%20and%20a%20sensory%20bathroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20fairytale%20homes%20and%20was%20built%20by%20architect%20brother%20duo%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20Kumar%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-7-1721822115-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-358330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20fairytale%20homes%20and%20was%20built%20by%20architect%20brother%20duo%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20Kumar%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Atik%20Bheda%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details.%20From%20a%20table%20made%20using%20discarded%20slate%20from%20an%20old%20home%E2%80%99s%20roof%20and%20a%20chandelier%20crafted%20from%20driftwood%20from%20the%20river%20Ganges%2C%20each%20piece%20of%20decor%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F285477%2Fsustainable-homes-energy-efficient-zero-waste-cut-electricity-water-bills-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20sustainable%20rendition%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20served%20is%20unique%20too%20%E2%80%94%20a%20simple%20meal%20of%20%3Cem%3Ealoo%20sabzi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(potato%20vegetable)%2C%20%3Cem%3Eroti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Edal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20dish%20made%20of%20lentils).%20When%20you%20aren%E2%80%99t%20feasting%20(your%20mouth)%20on%20the%20home-made%20fiestas%20and%20(your%20eyes)%20on%20the%20view%2C%20you%20can%20take%20part%20in%20a%20rafting%20session%20on%20the%20river%20Ganges%3B%20or%20go%20bird%20watching%20to%20spot%20the%20White-crested%20Himalayan%20Forest%20Laughing%20Thrush%20or%20the%20Red-billed%20Blue%20Magpie%3B%20or%20learn%20to%20brew%20%3Cem%3Ekombucha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20fizzy%20fermented%20drink)%3B%20or%20go%20foraging%20for%20mushrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomedays%2C%20the%20weather%20might%20play%20spoilsport%2C%20but%20dark%20skies%20are%20no%20deterrent%20to%20the%20mood%20at%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort.%20Candlelit%20dinners%20and%20torches%20come%20to%20the%20rescue.%20Applaud%20Raghav%20and%20Ansh%20for%20this%20work%20of%20art%20and%20they%20say%20it%20is%20the%20material%20%E2%80%98cob%E2%80%99%20that%20is%20the%20real%20hero.%20When%20pitted%20against%20other%20sustainable%20materials%2C%20cob%20emerges%20a%20winner%20for%20its%20durability%20and%20beauty%2C%20all%20tied%20into%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20is%20where%20these%20ideas%20are%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20space%20where%20artistry%20meets%20sustainability%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20circular%20design%2C%20research%2C%20build%2C%20and%20innovation%20studio%20in%20the%20woods%20in%20Rishikesh%2C%20Tiny%20Farm%20Lab%20is%20attempting%20to%20reinstill%20people%E2%80%99s%20beliefs%20in%20materials%20that%20were%20used%20centuries%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEspecially%20materials%20whose%20desirability%20has%20gone%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ansh%20adds.%20With%20a%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F354933%2Fombak-sustainable-furniture-shruthi-prakash-rattan-chairs-table-wall-decor-from-banana-fibres-in-indonesia-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiobased%20materials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20mycelium%20(a%20root-like%20structure%20of%20a%20fungus)%2C%20seaweed%20bioplastic%20and%20mud%2C%20the%20studio%20is%20an%20ode%20to%20how%20the%20best%20architecture%20is%20born%20out%20of%20the%20simplest%20ideas.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wanted%20to%20showcase%20that%20in%20a%20world%20where%20everything%20is%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20fast%20food%2C%20fast%20deliveries%2C%20speed%20dating%20%E2%80%94%20we%20can%20build%20something%20slow%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raghav%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20take%20mud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20decor%20is%20the%20homestay%20is%20made%20out%20of%20recycled%20wood%2C%20old%20doors%20and%20cob%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftiny-farm-fort-sustainable-home-6-1721813077-300