t%20is%20commonly%20found%20in%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20region%20of%20India.%20Devoured%20for%20its%20savoury%20taste%2C%20it%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Ebheranda%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Marathi%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekudampuli%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Malayalam%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekodampuli%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Tamil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Narayana%20passed%20away%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20his%20family%2C%20especially%20his%20son%2C%20has%20been%20carrying%20forward%20his%20legacy.%20Narayana%E2%80%99s%20estate%2C%20now%20managed%20by%20his%20son%2C%20boasts%20over%2010%2C000%20blooming%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Etrees%20that%20are%20actively%20producing%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20sat%20down%20with%20Ramesh%20to%20understand%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20vision%20and%20what%20Ramesh%20is%20doing%20to%20take%20it%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20leap%20of%20faith%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20fondly%20recalls%20when%20his%20father%20predicted%20that%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewould%20be%20in%20high%20demand%20in%20the%20future.%20Talking%20about%20the%20history%20of%20the%20estate%20and%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20dream%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20acquired%20our%20property%20in%201950%2C%20transforming%20what%20was%20then%20a%20dense%20forest%20into%20a%20plantation.%20Initially%2C%20we%20planted%20areca%2C%20rubber%2C%20coconut%2C%20jackfruit%2C%20and%20cashew.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ramesh%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20farming%20different%20plants%2C%20it%20was%20about%2015%20years%20ago%20that%20he%20began%20planting%20Kokum%2C%20anticipating%20its%20future%20demand%20due%20to%20its%20medicinal%20value.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20started%20growing%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebecause%20of%20his%20love%20for%20the%20fruit!%20Furthermore%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eplants%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20much%20water%20and%20grow%20well%20in%20the%20local%20climate%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20shares%20that%20his%20father%20planted%20around%2012%2C000%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eplants%2C%20of%20which%20approximately%2010%2C000%20have%20survived.%20%3Cem%3EKokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20highly%20sought%20after%20in%20North%20India%20for%20its%20use%20in%20making%20oils%20and%20beverages.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20confident%20that%20the%20price%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewould%20rise%2C%20and%20we%20decided%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20plants%20to%20mature.%20Initially%2C%20the%20price%20was%20around%20Rs%2010%20per%20kg%2C%20but%20it%20has%20now%20risen%20to%20Rs%20120%20to%20130%20per%20kg%2C%20and%20in%20some%20places%2C%20it%20can%20go%20up%20to%20Rs%20300%20per%20kg%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Narayan%20Rai%2C%20Ramesh's%20father.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537.jpg%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-500x261.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-768x401.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357728%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENarayan%20Rai%2C%20Ramesh%E2%80%99s%20father.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Narayan%20started%20farming%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eeveryone%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%20However%2C%20for%20him%2C%20this%20meant%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20native%20tree%2C%20which%20he%20did%20not%20want.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20initial%20challenges%20my%20father%20faced%20were%20significant.%20Farmers%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20a%20simple%20plant%20like%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecould%20solve%20their%20problems.%20Since%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20not%20well-known%20and%20had%20little%20demand%20in%20the%20market%2C%20farmers%20were%20reluctant%20to%20waste%20their%20time%20growing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESaving%20the%20native%20plant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20recalls%20that%20his%20father%20Narayan%20took%20it%20upon%20himself%20to%20raise%20awareness%20among%20the%20farmers.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20to%20demonstrate%20its%20effectiveness%20and%20partner%20with%20various%20organisations%20to%20showcase%20it.%20We%20tried%20to%20explain%20to%20the%20farmers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F266213%2Fkokum-sherbet-recipe-weight-loss-cholesterol-health-science-benefits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20medically%20beneficial%20it%20was%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20took%20around%2036%20to%2060%20months%20for%20the%20farmers%20to%20see%20results%20and%20recognise%20its%20benefits%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ramesh%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20farmers%20understood%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20idea%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20plant%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Etoo%2C%20he%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20were%20inspired%20after%20seeing%20our%20plantation%20and%20took%20plants%20from%20us.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20we%20have%20distributed%20around%202%2C00%2C000%20saplings%20to%20interested%20farmers.%20We%20charged%20Rs%205%20to%2012%20per%20sapling%2C%20but%20we%20stopped%20nursery%20production%20to%20preve